An Act relative to recycling cannabis infused beverages.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 SECTION 1. Section 321 of chapter 94 of the General Laws, as appearing in the 2022
2 Official Edition, is hereby amended by inserting after the word “water”, in line 6, the following
3 words:- , cannabis-infused beverages.
4 SECTION 2. Said section 321 of said chapter 94, as so appearing, is hereby further
5 amended by inserting after the definition of “Bottler” the following definition:-
6 “Cannabis-infused beverage”, a legally distributable beverage containing cannabinoid or
7 hemp or which has a cannabinoid profile, as those terms are defined in section 1 of chapter 94G.
8 SECTION 3. Section 323 of said chapter 94, as so appearing, is hereby amended by
9 inserting after the word “distributor”, in line 15, the words:- ; provided, that a distributor shall
10 not be required to pay any such handling fee for any cannabis-infused beverage container.
